The controls take a couple minutes to completely figure it out, but the dynamic between the fast soar option with the D-pad controlling ascent and descent and the slower flapping flight with the right side up and down arrows for ascent and descent, leaving the D-pad to control forward and backward flight make for a fair varierty of flight controls. All that, and you can gently change the flight angle by touching and dragging the screen.  I love how you can land and walk. The environment looks really cool. I must say, I'm incredibly impressed with the smooth control of diving down and darting past animals on the ground. It's not laggy at all! I was afraid it would become a debacle like the predator vision from the panther sim (which I was really hoping would be fixed, as I was so excited about that!) but it's not. It'll just take some practice to get used to it is all. Oh, and this was after 5 mins of playing. I'm going to go play more now! Wow, the passing of shadows and progression of the sun overhead and the colors of the sky during the day is magnificent. The textures of the rocks, trees, grass, and water are sharper than your previous sims. It's so easy to starve in this game.
